
                                            Team doctor Konrad von Hagen says that Etzebeth has a good chance of recovering from the leg injury he picked up in the Springbok’s 18-17 victory over France in Paris.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Springbok captain Eben Etzebeth is likely to be available for the Test match against Italy in Padova on Saturday.  Team doctor Konrad von Hagen says that Etzebeth has a good chance of recovering from the leg injury he picked up in the Springbok’s 18-17 victory over France in Paris.  Malcom Marx is also hopeful of participation in Padova, after his MRI scan revealed no serious damage to his shoulder.  Marx will however be given until Thursday to prove his fitness for Saturday.  Kick-off is at 15:00. 